# Trivy README

## 🧰 Prerequisites
- Docker installed on the host
- Outbound network access for initial Trivy DB download, or saved image with latest definitions.
- Directory structure located at /var/lib/containers/trivy
- Trivy image built locally or imported for offline use


## 📝 Description
An operator-friendly container scanning environment built around the latest Trivy image.
Provides vulnerability reports, CycloneDX SBOMs, and exportable ZIP bundles for IA review.
Designed for reproducibility, auditability, and future offline support.
For this to work offline, the latest Trivy image would need to be saved,
exported and imported into an offline container environment.

```menu
===============================================
           Trivy Scanning Menu
===============================================

 1) Run Vulnerability Scan (All Images)
 2) Run SBOM Scan (All Images)
 3) Update Trivy DB
 4) Export Scan Reports
 5) Import Latest Image + DB
 6) Exit

Select an option:
```

## 📂 Purpose
This suite standardizes how container images are scanned across environments.
All scans run inside a controlled Docker container with host-mounted directories.
Output includes JSON vulnerability reports and CycloneDX SBOMs in .cdx, .json,
or .xml formats. The workflow supports IA compliance, evidence generation, and
modernization planning. Added html reporting in March 2026 with summary counts.


## 📖 Notes
All scans run inside a container using docker run --rm for isolation.
All output is written to host-mounted directories for auditability.
Filenames include timestamps for traceability.
The workflow is designed to support future offline environments by allowing
the Trivy DB to be pre-downloaded and stored under db/.


## 🚀 Usage
The operator menu is available via the `menu` alias (configured in /etc/profile.d).
Type `menu` to use it.

- build_image: docker build -t trivy-local:latest .

- update_db: ./scripts/update-db.sh

- scan_single_vulnerability: ./scripts/scan-vuln.sh <container-name>

- scan_all_vulnerabilities: ./scripts/scan-all-vuln.sh

- scan_single_sbom: ./scripts/scan-sbom.sh <container-name>

- scan_all_sboms: ./scripts/scan-all-sbom.sh

- export_reports: ./scripts/export-reports.sh

- scan_menu: ./scripts/scan-menu.sh

- Scripts saved in /var/lib/containers/trivy/scripts.

## directory structure /var/lib/containers/trivy:

```tree
├── db
│   ├── metadata.json
│   └── trivy.db
├── Dockerfile
├── reports
└── scripts
    ├── export-image.sh
    ├── export-reports.sh
    ├── run-trivy.sh
    ├── scan-all-sbom.sh
    ├── scan-all-vuln.sh
    ├── scan-menu.sh
    └── update-db.sh
```

## scripts:

scan-vuln.sh: "Runs a vulnerability scan for a single container."

scan-all-vuln.sh: "Runs vulnerability scans for all defined containers."

scan-sbom.sh: "Generates a CycloneDX SBOM for a single container."

scan-all-sbom.sh: "Generates SBOMs for all defined containers."

trivy-menu.sh: "Saved in /etc/profile.d to create the menu alias.

update-db.sh: "Updates the Trivy vulnerability database stored under db/."

export-reports.sh: "Creates a timestamped ZIP file of all reports."

scan-menu.sh: "Provides an operator-friendly menu interface."


## 📦 SBOM Format Options
SBOMs default to CycloneDX `.cdx`. To change formats, modify the output extension in the SBOM scripts.

Supported formats:
- `.cdx`  – CycloneDX JSON (default)
- `.json` – CycloneDX JSON
- `.xml`  – CycloneDX XML
